Package: nimix
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Mixture Clustering and Regression with NIMBLE
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Achmad Syahrul", "Choir", email = "madsyair@stis.ac.id",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7088-0646"))
Description: A high-level extensible framework for fitting Bayesian mixture 
    and mixture-of-regressions models for clustering and regression, built 
    on top of the 'nimble' package ecosystem by de Valpine et al. (2017) 
    <doi:10.1080/10618600.2016.1172487>. It provides a unified S4 
    orchestration to seamlessly pair univariate and multivariate component 
    families, ranging from standard Gaussian and heavy-tailed distributions 
    to specialized neo-normal distributions. Supported paradigms include 
    infinite clustering via Dirichlet Process Mixture (DPM) models employing 
    the Chinese Restaurant Process, classic finite mixtures with a fixed 
    number of components, and spatially constrained mixtures governed by 
    Markov Random Field (MRF) Potts models on custom or lattice neighborhood 
    structures. The package automates data-scaled prior assignment, NIMBLE 
    model code generation, post-MCMC label switching correction using the 
    'label.switching' package, and efficient compile-once-reuse caching 
    mechanisms to minimize C++ compilation overhead.
